# npm lockfile — match CI

This repo pins **`npm@11.16.0`** via `packageManager` in `package.json`. CI (Node 24) runs `npm ci` — lockfiles generated with a different npm major can fail `npm ci`.

## When editing dependencies or bumping version

1. Regenerate the lockfile with the pinned npm:
   ```bash
   npx npm@11.16.0 install
   ```
2. Verify clean install:
   ```bash
   rm -rf node_modules && npx npm@11.16.0 ci
   ```
3. Commit `package.json` and `package-lock.json` together.

## Do not

- Run `npm install` with an unpinned npm version and commit the lockfile without verifying `npx npm@11.16.0 ci`
- Use `npm install --package-lock-only` as the only lockfile update for version bumps
- Commit `package.json` version changes without an updated `package-lock.json`

## Before push

```bash
npm run validate
```
